Regulatory Disclosures – United Kingdom and the United States of America
Arrowgrass Capital Partners LLP (“Arrowgrass UK”) is authorised and regulated by the United Kingdom Financial Conduct Authority ("FCA"). Additionally, in accordance with the requirements of the United States Investment Advisers Act of 1940 ("Advisers Act"), both Arrowgrass Capital Partners (US) LP ("Arrowgrass US") and Arrowgrass UK , together referred to as “Arrowgrass”, are registered as investment advisers with the United States Securities and Exchange Commission (“SEC”). Arrowgrass UK will comply with the Advisers Act with respect to U.S. clients only.
The information within this website is issued by Arrowgrass to sophisticated investors who are professional clients or eligible counterparties under the Rules of the FCA and “Accredited Investors” as defined in Regulation D promulgated under the U.S Securities Act 1933, as amended (the “Securities Act”) and “Qualified Purchasers” as defined under the U.S Investment Company Act 1940, as amended (the “Company Act”).
Access to this website from certain countries may be restricted by law and you are required to determine that you are permitted to access it.
Most if not all of the protections provided by the United Kingdom regulatory system will not apply to investments in the products detailed within this website.
The information within this website is unsuitable for any other party and any such other party should exit this website immediately. If you are unsure as to whether or not you qualify, please contact Arrowgrass.
